The paper is about evaluating communication protocol languages for engineering multiagent systems, which falls under the category of multiagent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses different programming models and abstractions for interactions among agents, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also touches upon the architecture of multiagent systems, which could be relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
